 policing -- t15 Moving to the inevitability of evidence based policing -- t16 Why is evidence based policing growing and what challenges lie ahead? -- t17 A practical approach to evidence based policing -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aOver the past ten years, the field of evidence-based policing (EBP) has grown substantially, evolving from a novel idea at the fringes of policing to an increasingly core component of contemporary policing research and practice. Examining what makes something evidence-based and not merely evidence-informed, this book unifies the voices of police practitioners, academics, and pracademics. It provides real world examples of evidence-based police practices and how police research can be created and applied in the field. Includes contributions from leading international EBP researchers and practitioners such as Larry Sherman, University of Cambridge, Lorraine Mazerrolle, University of Queensland, Anthony Braga, Northeastern and Craig Bennell, Carelton University.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aPolice administration. 0aPolice. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh1 aAndresen, Martin A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAntrobus, Emma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAriel, Barak, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBennell, Craig, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBennett, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlaskovits, Brittany, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBraga, Anthony A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCockcroft, Tom, econtributor.4ctb4http